1 Sess ion of the 60th Oklahoma Legislature and Enrolled House Joint
2 Resolution No. 1024 of the 2nd Session of the 60th Oklahoma
3 Legislature, shall be submitted to the people of Oklahoma for their
4 approval or rejection as and in the manner provided by law.
5 SECTION 2. The Chief Clerk of the House of Representatives,
6 immediately after the passage of this act, shall prepare and file
7 one copy thereof in accordance with Section 3 of Article V of the
8 Oklahoma Constitution one copy with the Secretary of State and one
9 copy with the Attorney General.
10 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
11 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
12 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
13 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
14
15 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON JOINT COMMITTEE ON APPROPRIATIONS
AND BUDGET, dated 04/20/2026 - DO PASS, As Amended.
